org.nd4j.linalg.api.blas

Interface Level2

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseLevel2, CpuLevel2, JcublasLevel2

    public interface Level2
    Level 2 blas implementations. Incx and other parameters are inferred from the given ndarrays. To avoid boxing, doubles are used in place of normal numbers. The underlying implementation will call the proper data type. This is a fortran 95 style api that gives us the efficiency and flexibility of the fortran 77 api Credit to: https://www.ualberta.ca/AICT/RESEARCH/LinuxClusters/doc/mkl81/mklqref/blaslev2.htm for the descriptions

      void gbmv(char order, char TransA, int KL, int KU, double alpha, INDArray A, INDArray X, double beta, INDArray Y)
      gbmv computes a matrix-vector product using a general band matrix and performs one of the following matrix-vector operations: y := alpha*a*x + beta*y for trans = 'N'or'n'; y := alpha*a'*x + beta*y for trans = 'T'or't'; y := alpha*conjg(a')*x + beta*y for trans = 'C'or'c'.
      void gbmv(char order, char TransA, int KL, int KU, IComplexNumber alpha, IComplexNDArray A, IComplexNDArray X, IComplexNumber beta, IComplexNDArray Y)
